<paragraph id="8BD236DDEF713A15FF78F835FA8AFE8E" blockId="32.[136,778,1737,2070]" lastBlockId="32.[810,1452,173,2002]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEF713A15FF78F835FDFEF7D4" bold="true" box="[189,571,2043,2070]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Diagnostic characters of female</emphasis>
. Body (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EF713A15FD5FF832FCC4F7D7" box="[666,769,2044,2070]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="33.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,200,1856]" captionTargetId="figure-18@33.[150,1438,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURE 18. Notodelphys reducta Illg &amp; Dudley, 1961, female. A, habitus, dorsal; B, anal somite and caudal rami, ventral; C, left caudal ramus, ventral; D, mandible; E, maxillule; F, maxilla; G, leg 5. Scale bars: A, 0.5 mm; B, 0.1 mm; C–F, 0.05 mm; G, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591187" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591187/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Fig. 18A</figureCitation>
) of dissected specimen 2.33 mm long. Caudal ramus (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EF713A15FABBFF63FCB8FF28" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="33.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,200,1856]" captionTargetId="figure-18@33.[150,1438,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURE 18. Notodelphys reducta Illg &amp; Dudley, 1961, female. A, habitus, dorsal; B, anal somite and caudal rami, ventral; C, left caudal ramus, ventral; D, mandible; E, maxillule; F, maxilla; G, leg 5. Scale bars: A, 0.5 mm; B, 0.1 mm; C–F, 0.05 mm; G, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591187" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591187/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Fig. 18B, C</figureCitation>
) about 3.3 times longer than wide (144×44 μm) and about 1.3 timeslongerthan anal somite (112×139 μm) (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EF713A15FCA2FEDDFC00FEEC" box="[871,965,275,301]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="33.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,200,1856]" captionTargetId="figure-18@33.[150,1438,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURE 18. Notodelphys reducta Illg &amp; Dudley, 1961, female. A, habitus, dorsal; B, anal somite and caudal rami, ventral; C, left caudal ramus, ventral; D, mandible; E, maxillule; F, maxilla; G, leg 5. Scale bars: A, 0.5 mm; B, 0.1 mm; C–F, 0.05 mm; G, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591187" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591187/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Fig 18B</figureCitation>
), ornamented with setules on outer margin; outer lateral seta located at 62% of ramus length.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEF713A15FC9AFE99FBF4FDDA" blockId="32.[810,1452,173,2002]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Rostrum tapering, as long as wide, with weakly bilobed apex. Antennule 15-segmented, but articulation betweensecondand thirdsegments incomplete.Antennary exopod represented by 2 large pinnate setae of subequal lengths; compound distal endopodal segment about 4 timeslongerthan wide.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEF713A15FC9AFDEDFBACFC72" blockId="32.[810,1452,173,2002]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
Labrumwithprominent posterolateral protuberances; posteromedian lobe broad, setulose on both sides and with several spinules in middle. Mandibular endopod with 4 and 9 setae on first and second segments, respectively (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EF713A15FCF7FD65FC5CFD04" box="[818,921,683,709]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="33.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,200,1856]" captionTargetId="figure-18@33.[150,1438,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURE 18. Notodelphys reducta Illg &amp; Dudley, 1961, female. A, habitus, dorsal; B, anal somite and caudal rami, ventral; C, left caudal ramus, ventral; D, mandible; E, maxillule; F, maxilla; G, leg 5. Scale bars: A, 0.5 mm; B, 0.1 mm; C–F, 0.05 mm; G, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591187" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591187/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Fig. 18D</figureCitation>
). Maxillule (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EF713A15FBE0FD65FB43FD04" box="[1061,1158,683,709]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="33.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,200,1856]" captionTargetId="figure-18@33.[150,1438,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURE 18. Notodelphys reducta Illg &amp; Dudley, 1961, female. A, habitus, dorsal; B, anal somite and caudal rami, ventral; C, left caudal ramus, ventral; D, mandible; E, maxillule; F, maxilla; G, leg 5. Scale bars: A, 0.5 mm; B, 0.1 mm; C–F, 0.05 mm; G, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591187" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591187/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Fig. 18E</figureCitation>
) with 10 setae on precoxal arthrite; endopod with trace of articulation, armed with total of 5 setae (2 distal seta longer and naked). Maxilla (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EF713A15FCF7FCDFFC5FFCEA" box="[818,922,785,811]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="33.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,200,1856]" captionTargetId="figure-18@33.[150,1438,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURE 18. Notodelphys reducta Illg &amp; Dudley, 1961, female. A, habitus, dorsal; B, anal somite and caudal rami, ventral; C, left caudal ramus, ventral; D, mandible; E, maxillule; F, maxilla; G, leg 5. Scale bars: A, 0.5 mm; B, 0.1 mm; C–F, 0.05 mm; G, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591187" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591187/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Fig. 18F</figureCitation>
) 5-segmented; syncoxa with 3 setae and 1 minute setule on first endite; endopod with 1, 1, and 4 setae on first to third segments, respectively. Maxilliped 3-segmented and armed with 10, 1, and 3 setae on first to third segments, respectively.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEF713A15FC9AFC75FCACFB41" blockId="32.[810,1452,173,2002]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
Exopods of legs 2–4 armed only with setae; setae on outer margins of exopods bluntly tipped. Leg 5 (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EF713A15FABBFC13FC9EFBD8" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="33.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,200,1856]" captionTargetId="figure-18@33.[150,1438,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURE 18. Notodelphys reducta Illg &amp; Dudley, 1961, female. A, habitus, dorsal; B, anal somite and caudal rami, ventral; C, left caudal ramus, ventral; D, mandible; E, maxillule; F, maxilla; G, leg 5. Scale bars: A, 0.5 mm; B, 0.1 mm; C–F, 0.05 mm; G, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591187" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591187/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Fig. 18G</figureCitation>
) protopod smooth, not defined from ventral surface of somite; outer protopodal process shorter than exopod; freeexopodalsegment quadrate 27×29 μm, with 2 unequal setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEF713A15FC9AFB49FC39FA70" blockId="32.[810,1452,173,2002]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEF713A15FC9AFB49FC59FB60" bold="true" box="[863,924,1159,1185]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Male</emphasis>
. Body 1.73 mmlong. Urosome 6-segmented: anal somite with several wart-like tubercles distally on dorsal and ventral surfaces. Caudal ramus about 3.2 times longer than wide, setulose on outer margin, with several wart-like tubercles in distal third of ventral surface. Antennule 10-segmented, geniculate between eighth and ninth segments; terminal segment with blunt tip. Leg 6 represented by 2 setae and 1 inner subdistal setule on genital operculum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3776556EF713A15FC9AFA74FABBF813" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEF713A15FC9AFA74FBE2F925" blockId="32.[810,1452,173,2002]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEF713A15FC9AFA74FC09FA15" bold="true" box="[863,972,1466,1492]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEF713A15FC18FA77FB0CFA12" authorityName="Illg &amp; Dudley" authorityYear="1961" box="[989,1225,1465,1491]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Notodelphys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reducta">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEF713A15FC18FA77FB0CFA12" box="[989,1225,1465,1491]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Notodelphys reducta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was first described by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFC4B2CEF713A15FC8BFA15FB85FA37" author="Illg, P. L. &amp; Dudley, P. L." box="[846,1088,1499,1526]" journalOrPublisher="Vie et Milieu, Supplement" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" pagination="1 - 126" part="12" refId="ref329073" refString="Illg, P. L. &amp; Dudley, P. L. (1961) Notodelphyid copepods from Banyuls-sur Mer. Vie et Milieu, Supplement 12, 1 - 126." title="Notodelphyid copepods from Banyuls-sur Mer" type="journal article" year="1961">Illg &amp; Dudley (1961)</bibRefCitation>
from the French Mediterranean coast. Subsequently, this copepod was reported also from Naples, 
<collectingCountry id="F37A764DEF713A15FC40F9D1FC7DF9F8" box="[901,952,1567,1593]" name="Italy" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Italy</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFFC4B2CEF713A15FC03F9D1FB6EF9FB" author="Illg, P. L. &amp; Dudley, P. L." box="[966,1195,1567,1594]" journalOrPublisher="Pubblicazioni della Stazione Zoologica di Napoli" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" pagination="373 - 451" part="34" refId="ref329106" refString="Illg, P. L. &amp; Dudley, P. L. (1965) Notodelphyid copepods from the vicinity of Naples. Pubblicazioni della Stazione Zoologica di Napoli, 34, 373 - 451." title="Notodelphyid copepods from the vicinity of Naples" type="journal article" year="1965">Illg &amp; Dudley, 1965</bibRefCitation>
). In both cases the host was 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEF713A15FC9FF98FFB9BF99A" authorityName=", MEDITS" authorityYear="2015" box="[858,1118,1601,1627]" class="Ascidiacea" family="Molgulidae" genus="Molgula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleurogona" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="appendiculata">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEF713A15FC9FF98FFB9BF99A" box="[858,1118,1601,1627]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Molgula appendiculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(as 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEF713A15FB4FF98FFA67F99A" authority="Lacaze-Duthiers, 1877" authorityName="Lacaze-Duthiers" authorityYear="1877" baseAuthorityName="Heller" baseAuthorityYear="1877" box="[1162,1442,1601,1627]" class="Ascidiacea" family="Molgulidae" genus="Ctenicella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stolidobranchia" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="appendiculata">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEF713A15FB4FF98FFA67F99A" box="[1162,1442,1601,1627]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Ctenicella appendiculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEF713A15FC99F9AAFC10F9BC" authorityName="Illg &amp; Dudley" authorityYear="1961" box="[860,981,1635,1662]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Notodelphys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reducta">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEF713A15FC99F9AAFCAAF9BC" box="[860,879,1636,1661]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">N</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B919EACFEF713A15FC45F9ADFC10F9BC" box="[896,981,1635,1661]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">reducta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the only known copepod associate of this ascidian. The ascidians 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEF713A15FBA1F948FB16F95E" authorityName="Drasche" authorityYear="1884" box="[1124,1235,1669,1695]" class="Ascidiacea" family="Molgulidae" genus="Molgula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleurogona" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="helleri">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEF713A15FBA1F948FB16F95E" box="[1124,1235,1669,1695]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">M. helleri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEF713A15FACFF948FA44F95E" authorityName="Kupffer" authorityYear="1875" box="[1290,1409,1669,1695]" class="Ascidiacea" family="Molgulidae" genus="Molgula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleurogona" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="occulta">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEF713A15FACFF948FA44F95E" box="[1290,1409,1669,1695]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">M. occulta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are reported here for the first time and constitute new host records for 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEF713A15FC6EF904FBDAF922" authorityName="Illg &amp; Dudley" authorityYear="1961" box="[939,1055,1737,1763]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Notodelphys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reducta">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEF713A15FC6EF904FBDAF922" box="[939,1055,1737,1763]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">N. reducta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEF713A15FC9AF925FABBF813" blockId="32.[810,1452,173,2002]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<bibRefCitation id="EFFC4B2CEF713A15FC9AF925FB9AF8C7" author="Illg, P. L. &amp; Dudley, P. L." box="[863,1119,1771,1798]" journalOrPublisher="Vie et Milieu, Supplement" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" pagination="1 - 126" part="12" refId="ref329073" refString="Illg, P. L. &amp; Dudley, P. L. (1961) Notodelphyid copepods from Banyuls-sur Mer. Vie et Milieu, Supplement 12, 1 - 126." title="Notodelphyid copepods from Banyuls-sur Mer" type="journal article" year="1961">
Illg &amp; 
<collectingRegion id="49A9F83FEF713A15FC70F925FBC2F8C4" box="[949,1031,1771,1797]" country="United Kingdom" name="Dudley" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Dudley</collectingRegion>
(1961)
</bibRefCitation>
mentioned that this species differed from every known species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEF713A15FB39F8C3FA4DF8E6" authorityName="Allman" authorityYear="1847" box="[1276,1416,1805,1831]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Notodelphys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEF713A15FB39F8C3FA4DF8E6" box="[1276,1416,1805,1831]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Notodelphys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the reduction of the protopod of leg 5. We infer that this description refers to the lack of a basal articulation between the protopod of leg 5 and the somite, as observed in our specimens, as well as the relatively small size of the outer protopodal process bearing the outer basal seta.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
